George O'Brien (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_O%27Brien_(actor) 0 George O'Brien (April 19, 1899 – September 4, 1985) was an American actor, popular during the silent film era and into the talkie era of the 1930s, best known today as the lead actor in F. W. Murnau's 1927 film Sunrise: A Song of Two Humans.
